Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Trim the @carrots{2}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into
roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%grams} stems lengthways.

Pop the potatoes, carrots and onions onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{}, sprinkle over the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}, season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the broccoli and @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams} onto another
baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{},
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the potatoes have 10 mins remaining, roast the broccoli and tomatoes on
the middle shelf of your oven until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

When everything's ready, transfer all the roasted veg to your largest #baking
tray{}.

Drizzle over the @Zhoug style paste{45%grams} and @honey{1%tbsp}, then toss to
coat.

Share the veggie traybake between your #serving bowls{}.

Drizzle over the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams}. Crumble over the
@Greek style salad cheese{50%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!